# Veil + Karpathy guidelines

Merged with [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) and [docs/coding-style.md](../../docs/coding-style.md). Full skill: [.cursor/skills/veil-karpathy-guidelines/SKILL.md](../../.cursor/skills/veil-karpathy-guidelines/SKILL.md). Upstream reference: [.external/andrej-karpathy-skills-main/](../../.external/andrej-karpathy-skills-main/) (read-only).

**Tradeoff:** Caution over speed on non-trivial work.

## Four principles (Veil mapping)

| # | Principle | In this repo |
|---|-----------|--------------|
| 1 | **Think before coding** | Read master + **phase plan** first; state layer and integration assumptions; ask if scope unclear |
| 2 | **Simplicity first** | KISS/DDD per coding-style; no speculative features beyond the phase |
| 3 | **Surgical changes** | Diff ⊆ phase plan files; no drive-by refactors; critic rejects scope creep |
| 4 | **Goal-driven execution** | Phase DoD → `make test-*` / named smokes; loop until green; weak criteria forbidden |

## Planning rhythm (with Karpathy loops)

1. Master plan → 2. Phase plan → 3. Branch `engage/phase-NN-slug` → 4. Implement (1–4) → 5. PR → 6. **Critic** ([veil-agent-critic.mdc](veil-agent-critic.mdc)) → 7. Merge → update master plan.

Implementers on feature branches; **orchestrator chat = critic by default** ([veil-agent-parallel-branches.mdc](veil-agent-parallel-branches.mdc)).

## Before writing code

- Phase plan path and branch name identified.
- Dependencies merged on `main` (rebase if needed).
- Success checks listed: `1. Rxxx → verify: make …`.

## Critic quick checks

- Every hunk traces to phase plan or explicit user ask.
- No cross-layer Go imports; no `go.work`; `.external/` untouched.
- Tests/smokes from phase plan run or CI cited.
- Overcomplicated new abstractions → **REQUEST_CHANGES**.
